init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: if this is a joke or not.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: he's always been a quick texter.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: you've never known him to not respond to a text.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You decide to call him instead.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK picks up on the first ring.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I got this letter from you and I was just calling to make sure it wasn't a joke."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: he's a little offended that you'd think he'd pull a prank like that.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I didn't send you a letter, Barack.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Well, I have it right here on my bedside table."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Well, it says 'I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Well, why don't you call the number and see what happens?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The phone rings once, twice, three times...and then a voice answers.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the voice belongs to none other than John F. Kennedy.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK is just as confused as you are.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: this is definitely JFK on the other end of the line.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I don't know how to cook."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK is in one world and the man who answered your call is in another.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: , you're not sure what else to think.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: you decide to go with it.
